==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Organogen
<hw>Or*gan"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Organo-</ets> + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A name given to any one of the four elements, carbon, hydrogen,
oxygen, and nitrogen, which are especially characteristic ingredients of
organic compounds; also, by extension, to other elements sometimes found
in the same connection; as sulphur, phosphorus, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Organogenesis</ent>⟦br⟧
